aa(lp173
VHope is personal. Hope is something
p174
aVthat no one can give to you.
p175
aVYou have to choose to believe in hope.
p176
aVYou have to make it yourself.
p177
aVIn North Korea, I made it myself.
p178
aVHope brought me to America.
p179
aVBut in America, I didn't know what to do,
p180
aVbecause I had this overwhelming freedom.
p181
aVMy foster father at that dinner gave me a direction,
p182
aVand he motivated me and gave me a purpose
p183
aVto live in America.
p184
aa(lp185
VI did not come here by myself.
p186
aVI had hope, but hope by itself is not enough.
p187
aVMany people helped me along the way to get here.
p188
aVNorth Koreans are fighting hard to survive.
p189
aVThey have to force themselves to survive,
p190
aVhave hope to survive,
p191
aVbut they cannot make it without help.
p192
aa(lp193
VThis is my message to you.
p194
aVHave hope for yourself,
p195
aVbut also help each other.
p196
aVLife can be hard for everyone, wherever you live.
p197
aVMy foster father didn't intend to change my life.
p198
aVIn the same way, you may also change someone's life
p199
aVwith even the smallest act of love.
p200
aVA piece of bread can satisfy your hunger,
p201
aVand having the hope will bring you bread
p202
aVto keep you alive.
p203
aVBut I confidently believe that
p204
aVyour act of love and caring
p205
aVcan also save another Joseph's life
p206
aVand change thousands of other Josephs
p207
aVwho are still having hope to survive.
p208
aa(lp209
VThank you.
